"{\"_values\": {\"num\": 47, \"title\": \"OKC Thunder Must Find New Arena Naming Rights Partner As Chesapeake Energy Terminates Agreement\", \"url\": \"https://www.forbes.com/sites/nicholascrain/2021/04/20/okc-thunder-in-process-of-securing-new-naming-rights-partner-amidst-chesapeake-energys-agreement-termination/\", \"description\": \"Chesapeake Energy Corporation filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy in June of 2020 before ultimately emerging in February of 2021 after financial restructuring and a plan to shed roughly $7.8 billion in debt.\", \"author\": \"Nick Crain\", \"content\": [\"Chesapeake Energy Corporation filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy in June of 2020 before ultimately emerging in February of 2021 after financial restructuring and a plan to shed roughly $7.8 billion in debt. Headquartered in Oklahoma City, this series of events had major implications on jobs across the country and the economy of Oklahoma as a whole. Additionally, Chesapeake Energy owned the naming rights to the arena that hosts Oklahoma\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds only major professional sports franchise, the Oklahoma City Thunder.\\u00a0\", \"Chesapeake Energy signed a contact for the naming rights to the arena in Oklahoma City in 2011. It was a a 12-year naming rights deal worth $3 million for the initial season and increased by three percent each year following. Although it was unclear how Chesapeake\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds restructuring would affect contracts like this, a final decision was made known today.\", \"In a \", \" on Tuesday, the Thunder announced Chesapeake Energy Corporation had informed them that as part of its recently completed restructuring, it is terminating its arena naming rights agreement with the team, effective immediately.\\u00a0\", \"This means that the franchise will now pivot to focus on identifying a new long-term naming rights partner, while the building will continue to be called Chesapeake Energy Arena in the meantime.\\u00a0\", \"\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdAs we move toward a transition to a new naming rights partner for our arena, we would like to recognize our extraordinary history with Chesapeake Energy,\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd said Clayton I. Bennett, chairman of the Oklahoma City Thunder. \\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdFor a decade, the arena has proudly bore its name and we thank Chesapeake, one of our founding partners, for its loyal support and partnership.\", \"Located in the heart of Downtown Oklahoma City, Bennett would go on to talk about the impact the arena has made on the community and how it has become a hub for growth and expansion of other landmarks in the city like Scissortail Park and the new Oklahoma City Convention Center, along with the Omni Hotel across the street.\\u00a0\", \"\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdAs Chesapeake Energy Arena, our building has been home to so many exciting and historic moments and events,\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd said Bennett. \\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdAs we look to forge a new partnership for naming rights, we will identify a partner who will help build on that history and be the centerpiece of our growing, modern and vibrant downtown environment.\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd\", \"For Chesapeake as a business, this is another decision on their path to restoring their balance sheet. Chief Executive Officer Doug Lawler gave a statement on the positive relationship between Chesapeake Energy and the Oklahoma City Thunder over the past decade.\\u00a0\", \"\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdWe have greatly appreciated our long-standing partnership with the Thunder, and while our commitment to restoring our balance sheet and increasing our competitiveness required us to terminate our naming rights agreement, as proud Oklahomans, we will continue to strongly support the team,\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd said Lawler.\", \"One of the few teams to not allow fans in their arena this season for home games, the Oklahoma City Thunder have played in a nearly empty stadium this season with only players, team staff, arena staff and media allowed inside. Although the structure hosts more than just Thunder basketball events, there are only 14 more games left in the regular season for the team, seven of which are at home.\"]}}"